HEADWORD: Swindle
<hw>Swin"dle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Swindled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Swindling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[See
<er>Swindler</er>.]</ety> <def>To cheat defraud grossly, or with
deliberate artifice; <as>as, to <ex>swindle</ex> a man out of his
property</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lammote . . . has <qex>swindled</qex> one of them out of three
hundred livres.</q> <rj><qau>Carlyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swindle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Swindle
<hw>Swin"dle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or process of swindling; a
